channel.title: Need help, found out runescapes ip address
channel.description:
Ok, me and my friend came to the point of trying to get runescapes ip address, so we did.
start -> run -> cmd -> start nslookup -> www.runescape.com -> 65.39.250.68 (and many more ips).
in nslookup we typed in www.runescape.com and came up with loads of ips address's, so we took one (65.39.250.68) and pasted it in the browser, press go.. and we are at www.runescape.com but it didnt redirect, in the browser it still said http://65.39.250.68 so then we thoght it could be a server, so we went to http://www.ip-adress.com/ typed in 65.39.250.68 and pressed ip look up we got a bunch of info and a map of the location.
IP address info: IP address: 65.39.250.68 (copy) IP country: United States IP Address state: IP Address city: New York IP postcode: 10004 IP latitude: 40.688801 IP longitude: -74.020302 ISP: Peer 1 Network Organization: JAGEX LIMITED
see? organization jagex limited, ip address city: newyork.. so yeah this ip is the newyorks server..i think.
so we then were lost, so we thoght of typing it in moparscape lolz, so we typed in a real username and password, and then the ip..we got a error.
now, we are at a point of being lost, we thoght this info could be usefull to someone, so thats why ive posted it. any help appeciated.

Well I couldn’t even IP ban them because they logged in and out too fast. (Plus I was hosting the server soo ya) but I did get the IP. I see it happen to peoples servers all the time, but idk. I think its pretty stupid doing something like that.

item.dc:creator: @Greeny Greeny
item.description:
@Greeny wrote:

[quote=“pplsuqbawlz, post:22, topic:75888”]This is known as a “basic” and ultra noobish Denial of Service attack. It wont shut down the servers, it will just make you blocked/banned temporarily. It doesn’t take them down for anyone else; get your facts straight. It’s actually more efficient to write an attack that starts pinging on multiple threads un-ending if you really want to attack, plus it’s necessary to “mask” yourself in some means.[/quote] Let’s not forget that doing so will probably end in legal actions being taken against you. and Dell451, if you think you can ping an RS server multiple times and overload it you aren’t too intelligent. 2000 People can be playing on a server communicating with it constantly with little or no lag. It would take a massive attack to take down a game server and you would be IP banned before you even got properly started - the chances of finishing the attack would be next to none.
